<DOC><DOCNO> AP900319-0278 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-19-90 2129EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-Heinz-RJRNabisco     03-19 0204</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Heinz-RJR Nabisco,0211</SECOND><HEAD>Heinz Interested in Buying Grey Poupon, A1</HEAD><DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   H.J. Heinz Co. said Monday it is interested inbuying RJR Nabisco's A1 steak sauce and Grey Poupon mustard linesbut that no talks on a possible deal have occurred.   Heinz is interested in the products although it already producesbarbecue sauce under its Heinz 57 label and also manufacturesmustard, said Ted Smyth, spokesman for the Pittsburgh-based foodmaker.   On Saturday, Smyth said RJR Nabisco and Heinz were discussing apossible sale and that Heinz Chairman Anthony J. O'Reilly announcedthe talks in a meeting with Wall Street analysts last week.   However, Heinz issued a statement Monday saying the company wasnot and had not been in talks about Grey Poupon and A1. But Smythsaid on Monday that the company was interested in those brands.   The investment firm Kohlberg Kravis Roberts andamp; Co. paid $24.53billion last year to take RJR Nabisco private in the largestcorporate takeover ever. The firm has been selling selected assetsto reduce its debt load.   RJR Nabisco already has sold its Del Monte fresh fruit andprocessed food businesses, some of its foreign operations and itsBaby Ruth and Butterfinger candy business.</TEXT></DOC>